# Workspace Command Docs

Workspace commands manage the project-local files that agents read before operating in a repository.

## Common Workflows

- Create a contract with `enclosure workspace sync init`.
- Start workspace drilldowns with `enclosure workspace health`.
- Refresh packaged shared assets with `enclosure workspace sync update`.
- Validate rule documents with `enclosure workspace rules`.
- Inspect and render local scaffolding recipes with `enclosure workspace recipe`.

## Source Of Truth

- `--help` is the source for exact syntax and options.
- `--docs` explains when and why to use a command.
- `--llm` explains how an agent should interpret command output.

## Related Commands

- `enclosure workspace sync --docs`
- `enclosure workspace health --docs`
- `enclosure workspace rules --docs`
- `enclosure workspace recipe --docs`
